caption.text:
RESUMO DO JOGO:

As mudanças na jogabilidade do jogo se concentram principalmente em um novo recurso chamado VOLTA Football. O modo, que se traduz em 'retorno' em português, concentra-se no futebol de rua, em vez dos jogos tradicionais associados a série da FIFA. Incluirá várias opções para jogar em três contra três, quatro contra quatro e cinco contra cinco, bem como com regras profissionais de futsal. O modo incorporará o mesmo mecanismo, mas enfatiza a habilidade e o jogo independente, em vez do jogo tático ou em equipe.

Além disso, os jogadores terão a opção de personalizar seus jogadores por gênero, roupas, sapatos, chapéus e tatuagens. Após a conclusão da série de três partes "The Journey" no FIFA 19, os jogadores agora podem ter um modo de história semelhante no VOLTA Football, que seria jogado com o próprio personagem do jogador.

Também serão feitas alterações no modo tradicional 11 vs 11 para incentivar mais criação de espaço individual e fora da bola. Novas mecânicas de pênaltis e de cobrança de falta serão implementadas e serão feitas atualizações na física da bola.

O VOLTA Football incluirá 17 locais, cada um oferecendo uma experiência única. Além de um armazém e estacionamento genéricos, os jogadores também podem competir em  Amsterdam, Barcelona, Berlin, Buenos Aires, Cape Town, Lagos, London, Los Angeles, Mexico City, Miami, New York City, Paris, Rio de Janeiro, Rome e Tokyo.

I just hope next time they’ll not continue to break the “no free to play content” rule. That was REALLY annoying.

“Andrew and I have been playing video games together for years now. It’s kept us in touch and genuinely been something I’m grateful for more and more each year…” Andrew Voor and Gabriel Murgueytio started a collaborative video game YouTube channel, (pretty much every young dudes dream) but there’s a lot more behind it than what you’d think. These games have helped them keep in touch and maintain consistency in each others lives, and now they’re building a community online and are encouraging others to have fun with their friends too.  Today I sit down with the incredible Co-op Bros to talk about the importance of failure, friendship and video game culture. This isn’t just a conversation about Super Smash Bros… This is a conversation about doing what you love, and the importance of community and health in the digital world.  Get your gaming systems out, put on the pod and enjoy it! HORI lanzará volantes de Mario Kart para Nintendo Switch. 
HORI  está preparando 2 productos diferentes: el Mario Kart Racing Wheel y el Mario Kart Racing Wheel DX. La diferencia es que la edición DX tiene botones adicionales como ZL y ZR en el volante y paletas más grandes para cambiar velocidades. 
Por el momento están confirmados para Japón. El Racing Wheel tendría un precio de $71.25 USD y el DX $142.71 USD.

Does anyone else Remember Minecade? Well, if you don't, then I can't say I blame you. Minecade was a server network that was popular in the Java edition of Minecraft for a short while. One of the most popular games on it was Super Craft Bross, which was basically Kit PVP with double jumping and special abilities. Sethbling, a Minecraft YouTuber who specializes in making mechanics and contraptions, was a pretty big face of the server for a while.

However, as time went by, things around the server started to go downhill. Updates for Super Craft Bros. were few and far between. Balancing issues and bugs were rarely if ever, fixed. To make things worse, Minecraft's popularity was in a lull. It was around this time I quit playing on Minecade because the games I liked just weren't fun to play anymore.

Fast forward to now. With Minecraft getting a bit of an extra life when it comes to mainstream popularity, I wondered what Minecade has been up to. Last I checked, they could barely break 50 players, and those players were mostly on a rather basic creative server. When I went to the website, all I found was, well, this. The website is a mess. I’ve also checked around a few forums and can’t find much.

So. What happened to Minecade? I’ll keep looking.

caption.text:
Brand New Game Pickup: Dragon Quest XI S: Echoes of an Elusive Age Definitive Edition (Nintendo Switch)
Our main hero is back and his long quest is about to unfold. It's time to live the Legend of the Luminary and set out an adventure to reveal the answers the hero is looking for! Only this time, the Switch version allows you transition between a fully rendered 3D world to a classic 2D style! Game designed by Yuji Horii and character design beautifully done by the Legendary artist Akira Toriyama!
♡Who else picking up their copy this Friday? Feel free to share your thoughts and experience in the comments below. I'd love to hear from you guys! Take care and have a wonderful Happy Wednesday!♡
#nintendo #nintendoswitch #squareenix #squareenixgames #jrpg #dragonquest #jrpgfan #jrpgcollector #dragonquestxidefinitiveedition #hero #quest #adventure #destinyawaits #yujihorii #akiratoriyama #nintendofan #nintendocollector #nintendonerd #dragonquestxi #supernerd #gamerguy🎮🎮

Um dos cenários mais marcantes da história dos videogames é o de Sagat, com a estátua no fundo.
A grande curiosidade dessa publicação é a seguinte: vocês sabiam que essa estátua existe na vida real?
Ela se encontra na Tailândia, na cidade de Ayutthaya e representa o instante em que Buda entrou na nirvana antes da morte.
Em Bangkok existe uma estátua semelhante, que foi inspirada nessa de Ayutthaya, mas como dissemos, a verdadeira encontra-se nessa última cidade.
Alguém viu essa estátua ao vivo na Tailândia? Sabiam que ela existe de verdade? Conhecem mais algum cenário inspirado em objetos reais?
Participem do Sopre a Fita!!!

caption.text:
SPOILER WARNING!!!
This video contains minor/major spoilers for Xenoblade Chronicles and Xenoblade Chronicles 2 due to the dialogue exchanges between the characters. This is another video I absolutely love, as these post battle quotes give hints to certain connections between both games. Also Zeke is the best in everything he's in.

Also, received a received a FREE CIB James Bond 007: The Duel on Sega Genesis today!

James Bond 007: The Duel is a 1993 action video game featuring the character of the British secret agent James Bond. It was developed by The Kremlin and published by Domark for Sega's Mega Drive/Genesis and Master System video game consoles, and the Game Gear handheld game console. The Mega Drive version was also released in Japan by Tengen on 14 May 1993, under the title known as 007: Shitō.

Armed with a pistol, the player controls James Bond through various side-scrolling enemy bases to rescue female hostages and arm a bomb placed at a strategic point to destroy the base. Along the way, Bond must battle numerous thugs and familiar bosses. The game is often compared to Namco's Rolling Thunder series, although it was much less popular with the critics. (Source @wikipedia)

caption.text:
I decided to choose something from the catalog of games for PS4 and stopped on "Everything" ✨ (author @davidoreilly — I love his works; It's awesome!😌✨). It's an unusual game, it's an emotion-game, an abstraction, maybe even a bit of a installation-game. 
I've always wanted to get acquainted with this work, but all the time waiting for the right moment. 
And now it had come. 
I will try to play it not only on # PS4, but also in portable mode on #PSVita. 
I think it will be an interesting experience😊 .

title: The Last of Us Part II recebe trailer emocionante

caption.text:
Depois de mais de um ano de silêncio, Naughty Dog e Sony exibiram um novo trailer de The Last of Us Part II e, revelaram a data de lançamento do jogo: 21 de fevereiro de 2020.
Tudo mostrado em The Last of Us Part II até agora tinham sido paisagens muito bonitas, com um visual apurado, e com gameplay incrível. Porém não revelavam nada do enredo da nova jornada. Mas dessa vez foi possível ter mais noção do “ódio” que irá mover a agora jovem Ellie.
No trailer tem cutscene, gameplay, clickers, violência e um velho conhecido…

caption.text:
Finalmente, luego de tantas horas arreglando, mejorando y explotando al máximo mi creatividad, acabo de subir mi primer nivel a Super Mario Maker 2.
Espero que todos puedan jugarlo y lo disfruten tanto como yo disfruté haciéndolo.
El nivel usa las distintas mecánicas que hay disponible para los Thwomps, y me aseguré que tenga fases llenas de emoción y diversión.
Pese a que tiene una dificultad considerable (sobretodo para los más casuales) es posible completarlo luego de practicarlo, les recomiendo dedicarle tiempo.
Por cierto, si desean una dificultad aún mayor, es posible conseguir el Final Verdadero! Para conseguirlo, deberán recolectar las 8 monedas escondidas por todo el nivel (esto es totalmente opcional). Algunas requerirán una prueba de habilidad, y otras les obligaran a pensar un poco más (pero hay pistas escondidas en todo el nivel). Si deciden emprender esta aventura extra, les deseo mucha suerte!
Y nada más, mándenme sus opiniones, críticas y capturas cuando lo pasen, si llegan al True Ending con más razón! Mucha suerte y diviértanse!

Código: HY9-P1H-50G.
